SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 187
By Oliver
A RESOLUTION to honor Silver Sands Café on more than fifty
years of service to Nashville.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to recognize an
outstanding restaurant that has earned loyal customers and received critical accolades for its
mouth-watering soul food; and
WHEREAS, for more than five decades, Silver Sands Café has served the Nashville
community with some of the most delicious homemade Southern-style food available in Music
City; and
WHEREAS, popular family recipes have been passed down three generations, including
such staples as smothered pork chops, potatoes and onions, salmon croquettes, fried chicken,
macaroni and cheese, greens, hot-water cornbread, and so many more; and
WHEREAS, Silver Sands Café's selection is truly outstanding as is the owners'
commitment to friendly customer service; and
WHEREAS, located at 937 Locklayer Street, Silver Sands Cafe is a family-owned
restaurant that serves food "Just Like Mama Used To Make," as asserted by its motto and
attested to by a legion of satisfied customers; and
WHEREAS, an icon in Nashville for more than fifty years, Silver Sands Café is deserving
of our recognition; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor Silver Sands Café on more than fifty years
of service to Nashville, thank its owners and employees for providing delicious food to people
from all walks of life, and wish them all the best in their future endeavors.
